definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sugar","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sugar, to sprinkle sugar over"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sweeten, to add sugar"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to candy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get drunk, to become intoxicated"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be drunk, to be intoxicated"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intoxicant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wine"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكِرَ (sakira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drunkenness, intoxication, inebriety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكِرَ (sakira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"drunk"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of سُكَّار (sukkār, “bolt-lock”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Indo-European *ḱorkeh₂\nProto-Indo-Iranian *ćárkaraH\nProto-Indo-Aryan *śárkaraH\nSanskrit शर्क॑रा (śárkarā)\nGandhari 𐨭𐨐𐨪 (śakara)bor.\nMiddle Persian 𐭱𐭪𐭥 (šakar)bor.\nArabic سكر\nBorrowed from Middle Persian 𐭱𐭪𐭥 (šakar), borrowed from Gandhari 𐨭𐨐𐨪 (śakara), from Sanskrit शर्क॑रा (śárkarā), from Proto-Indo-Aryan *śárkaraH, from Proto-Indo-Iranian *ćárkaraH, from Proto-Indo-European *ḱorkeh₂ (“gravel”). For the vocalism from Middle Persian to Arabic, compare أُشَّق (ʔuššaq, “ammoniacum”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *šikar- (“alcoholic drink”). Cognate with Hebrew שֵׁכָר (šēḵār)."},"ipa":["/suk.kar/"]}